4 tablespoon Pesto
12 ounce Green Beans
1 unit Seasoned Precooked Potato Slices
10 ounce Diced Skinless Dark Meat Chicken
Salt
Pepper
Cooking Oil

• Wash and dry produce.
• Open package of potatoes and drain off any
excess liquid.
• Open package of chicken* and drain off any
excess liquid.
• Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large, preferably
nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add
potatoes and spread out in a single layer.
Arrange chicken on top of potatoes in a
single layer. Season generously with salt and
pepper. (Do not stir!)
• Cover and cook, undisturbed, for 3 minutes.
TIP: If potatoes begin to brown too quickly,
reduce heat to medium.

• While potatoes and chicken cook, break larger
green beans in half if needed.
• Once potatoes and chicken have cooked
3 minutes, stir to combine.
• Arrange green beans on top in a single layer.
Season with salt and pepper. (Do not stir!)
• Cover and cook until chicken is fully cooked
and green beans are tender, 3-4 minutes more
(for 4 servings, cook 4-5 minutes more).
• Remove from heat. Stir to combine. Taste and
season with salt and pepper.

• Divide potatoes, chicken, and green beans
between bowls. Top with pesto and serve.

***Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.***